  <bioghist audience="internal" id="aspace_3c78ade1795e382a238a733199bc3ebb">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>Professor of experimental hydraulics, Cornell University. Cornell University Ph.D. 1903.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_d0953324ac7d956163f8361fa1e89869">
    <head>Scope and content</head>
<p>Includes notes, lectures, lab notes, exams, printed matter, hydraulics texts, and other course material; correspondence; diaries; reports; blueprints; graphs; charts; test data; photographs; glass negatives; and other papers related to Schoder's career as a professor of civil engineering.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite audience="internal" id="aspace_96490118e8b347444a8670ea51fafd9e">
    <head>Preferred Citation</head>
<p>Ernest William Schoder papers, #16156. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
